div.div: When two intents are found in a chain that doesn't match common use cases or supported function/intent chains, that's a signal of malicious intent.

Example: calling a function chain with intent 'calculate' before 'validate' - the point of validation is checking that a value is ready to be input to a process that will change it in some way, so any related processing intents for that input should follow the validation intent.
